  "text": "A positive feedback loop might be established between the bioenergetic/biosynthetic demands and the epigenetically induced support of the CSC function and fate. Accordingly, the transcriptional activation of key nutrient-and energy-sensing pathways, i.e., mTOR and insulin receptor pathways, is an intrinsic process that occurs when differentiated populations of non-CSC breast cancer cells pass through dedifferentiating nuclear reprogramming-like processes to de novo development of CSC-like properties in vitro [CITATION_1] .",
